Reasoning: The paper deals with the analysis of text corpora and the modeling of topic networks, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. Specifically, the use of Volunteered Geographic Information (VGI) and Linguistic Multilayer Networks (LMN) suggests a focus on natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The study also involves the analysis of large datasets and the use of machine learning techniques, which are relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR), data mining (cs.DM), and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the concept of cognitive maps and the interpretation of the findings in the context of media and communication suggest a connection to social and information networks (cs.SI) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Overall, the paper covers a broad range of topics and could potentially fit into multiple sub-categories, but the focus on NLP and information retrieval makes cs.CL and cs.IR the most likely choices.
